        <heading>1924.  Mere representation of majority; reliance</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 1924.  Mere representation of majority; reliance
The mere representation of majority by an unemancipated minor does not preclude an action for rescission of the contract.  When the other party reasonably relies on the minor's representation of majority, the contract may not be rescinded.</p>
        </content>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=109171</p>
        </authorialNote>
